  "bookTitle": "Little Pharmacist",
  "bookId": 2,
  "firstAcquaintance": "A lively and adorable human girl with extensive knowledge of plants and pharmacy. For some reason, she was sold at a surprisingly low price in the slave market.",
  "personality": "Though a bit scatterbrained and prone to inappropriate behavior, her cheerful and adorable demeanor easily wins people over.",
  "like": "Grilled meat",
  "familiarData": "Metori was a girl living deep in the forest. She was captured by slave hunters while gathering herbs and sold into slavery.\nWith her knowledge of pharmacy, she became the guild's pharmacist. In truth, she has no particular talent for making medicine. Her real gift lies in identifying plants. Without any tools, she can precisely determine a plant's medicinal properties by instinct alone. Using this ability, she has invented many medicines for the guild, making her an indispensable member.\nHer bubbly and goofy personality makes her the mood-maker of the guild. She can laugh heartily no matter the situation. She occasionally does things at inappropriate times, but everyone usually forgives her.\nShe absolutely loves grilled meat, a passion she shares with her master. Being able to eat grilled meat every day at the guild makes her very happy.",
